@node Auto-save directory for new buffers
@section Auto-save directory for new buffers

@vindex simple-extras-new-buffer-auto-save-dir
The user option @code{simple-extras-new-buffer-auto-save-dir} specifies the directory in which auto-save files for new, non-file-visiting buffers are stored. These are buffers with names matching @samp{untitled} that have no associated file on disk (@ref{Auto-save for new buffers}).

The default value is derived from @code{no-littering-var-directory}, placing auto-save files at @samp{var/auto-save/new-buffers/} beneath the @samp{no-littering} data directory. The type is @code{directory}. If the specified directory does not exist when the option is set, it is created automatically via the @code{:set} function.

You would change this if you want auto-save files for untitled buffers stored in a different location, for example on a RAM disk for faster writes or in a directory that is excluded from backups.

